Example: Create a branch for the created repository and use Apache to replace Nginx.
Step 1 Create a branch.
Run the following command to create a branch and name it "apache":
[root@controller MyGit]# git checkout -b apache
In the current branch, run the following command to replace Nginx with httpd in the
nginx.yml file:
[root@controller MyGit]# sed -i "s/nginx/httpd/g" nginx.yml
After the operation is complete, check the current repository status.
Push files in the branch to the repository.


